Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.41,0:00:03.37,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Flowing water has no form.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.37,0:00:05.00,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A blowing wind can't be seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.00,0:00:06.63,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}All cases can be freely deduced!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.63,0:00:08.83,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The language of flowers has a deep meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.83,0:00:10.83,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Songs and murderous intent cross the barriers of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.83,0:00:12.49,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.49,0:00:14.39,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.39,0:00:16.39,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.40,0:02:03.25,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}We got a request for a job from Yoshinori Kana, chairman of the Kana Amusement Group.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.67,0:02:06.31,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He asked us to attend a party
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.31,0:02:10.61,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and protect his wife, Misaki{\rHonorifics - Narration Off\be10}-san{\r\be10}, who was being stalked by someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.56,0:02:15.43,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There was a blackout during the party,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.99,0:02:17.85,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and Misaki{\rHonorifics - Narration Off\be10}-san{\r\be10} was attacked in her room.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.26,0:02:25.91,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Suspicion fell on Gerard Tenma, the main guest of the party.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.40,0:02:30.47,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}However, Gerard Tenma himself was murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.50,0:02:48.17,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The murder weapon is the knight's sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.78,0:02:52.80,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A tuning fork, used to tune the piano...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.16,0:02:55.26,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I wonder what this scratch is...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.39,0:02:59.87,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And what is the piano stool doing over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.40,0:03:03.74,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's stuck under the large sofa.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.88,0:03:06.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You stay put!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.94,0:03:09.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone, please move over to the waiting room,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.28,0:03:11.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so that we can keep the crime scene as is.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.71,0:03:12.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Gerard...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.49,0:03:21.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yoshinori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, are you the one\Nwho killed Mr. Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.28,0:03:24.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,N-No! It wasn't me!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.04,0:03:26.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was in the waiting room! Right here!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.45,0:03:31.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tenma ignored me and went into the piano room alone!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.65,0:03:35.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I had no choice and was about to sit in the chair,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.86,0:03:38.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I heard a thump and a scream,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.35,0:03:39.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and when I went to look...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.62,0:03:42.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I found Tenma dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.33,0:03:48.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But at that time, everyone else was in the large reception room downstairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.51,0:03:49.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right, Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.90,0:03:52.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of all things, how could you...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.29,0:03:54.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I told you, I didn't do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.77,0:03:59.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You didn't like the fact that I decided on this whole thing by myself in the first place!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.53,0:04:04.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So when you found out that Sis and Tenma used to go with each other in the past,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.42,0:04:06.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you were enraged, weren't you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.81,0:04:08.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Well, that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.81,0:04:11.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, the Kana family is finished...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.30,0:04:14.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's too bad, chairman...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.07,0:04:19.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder who will take over the Kana Amusement Group now?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.76,0:04:21.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm innocent!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.65,0:04:23.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, did you see the killer?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.65,0:04:27.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.70,0:04:30.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I got there, there was\Nalready no one there...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.12,0:04:32.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.30,0:04:34.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When Misaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} led us in there,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.93,0:04:37.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the piano lid was closed, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.20,0:04:39.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder if Gerard{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} opened it...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.68,0:04:44.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No... In a room of this size, you can hear the piano well enough without opening the lid.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.88,0:04:46.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Gerard would never open it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.55,0:04:48.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.05,0:04:55.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The top lid of the piano was open even before Tenma came into the room!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.36,0:04:57.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means that...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.20,0:05:05.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the killer could have opened the lid of the piano beforehand to block our view...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.05,0:05:21.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only way out of this room is through the waiting room.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.40,0:05:26.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One of the windows was open,\Nbut below it is just a large drop to the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.70,0:05:31.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if the killer were to jump in,\Nit would be difficult to avoid the rocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.02,0:05:31.99,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.45,0:05:34.24,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There's a scratch on the window frame too...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.98,0:05:37.24,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It looks like a scratch from a string or something that scraped it...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.85,0:05:41.51,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's the same as when Misaki{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} was attacked!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.59,0:05:48.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If a rope were used, you could escape either up or down.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.62,0:05:51.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, that is a reasonable possibility...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.92,0:05:55.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But could someone flee that quickly?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.69,0:06:00.04,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A scratch made by the tip of the sword cutting through the floor, perpendicular...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.22,0:06:02.59,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This means...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.02,0:06:07.37,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Maybe...{start catalanning here on the next pass}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.15,0:06:20.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's position you all back where you were at the time of the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.57,0:06:23.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's all go to the next room.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.83,0:06:33.23,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The small chandelier on this side
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.23,0:06:35.55,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}is positioned higher than the big one over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.13,0:06:38.55,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}When we were brought in here,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.55,0:06:40.38,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I'm sure it was positioned lower.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.81,0:06:43.67,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.67,0:06:45.34,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There's another scratch here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.34,0:06:47.34,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It looks like the one by the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.06,0:06:53.95,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}So this is the chain that moves the chandelier up and down.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.85,0:06:56.75,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I guess it's easy to roll it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.19,0:07:05.35,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Only this box has no dust on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.31,0:07:13.07,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}"The Red Nocturne of Love"...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.58,0:07:18.18,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This song is a gift that Mr. Tenma dedicated to Misaki{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} ten years ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.21,0:07:20.61,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Wait a sec...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.61,0:07:23.18,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What does this mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.07,0:07:26.88,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.72,0:07:28.80,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}On the piano...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.15,0:07:37.18,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Is this blood?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.11,0:07:40.03,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}No, it's not...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.33,0:07:42.70,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Inside the piano too?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.97,0:07:47.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Kobayashi...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.10,0:07:49.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.75,0:07:51.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Lend me your ear, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.76,0:07:55.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The inspector said that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.88,0:07:58.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To look for a bust of Beethoven?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.09,0:08:01.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it really in the sea?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.19,0:08:03.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Good luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.34,0:08:12.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At any rate, I'll have to have you come to the station with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.82,0:08:14.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.20,0:08:16.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How many times do I have to tell you\Nto make you believe me?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.40,0:08:18.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Misaki! Help me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.40,0:08:19.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dear...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.54,0:08:24.12,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If this piece fits into that part...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.85,0:08:28.91,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Just as I thought!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.59,0:08:32.45,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This is the debris from the decoration up there!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.30,0:08:34.94,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Only that person could have committed the murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.11,0:08:40.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll take care of the company, Brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.97,0:08:46.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're already thinking of selling a memorial CD of Gerard Tenma, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.31,0:08:47.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How dare you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.34,0:08:57.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the one who attacked Misaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.12,0:09:03.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Megure...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.50,0:09:07.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like you said, this bust of Beethoven was found on the beach!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.57,0:09:10.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I never asked you to do such a thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.81,0:09:12.12,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Uh oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.12,0:09:13.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, what's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.11,0:09:19.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a scratch below the railing
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.52,0:09:22.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that seems to have been made by scraping a thin string or wire on it...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.40,0:09:24.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.23,0:09:26.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.22,0:09:28.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this string called?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.68,0:09:31.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't this the string you use when you go fishing?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.65,0:09:33.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's called fishing line.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.00,0:09:37.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector, there was fishing line\Nand this stick on that bust...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.08,0:09:39.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did you say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.60,0:09:40.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.68,0:09:43.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The scratch on the railing was made by the fishing line scraping against it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.96,0:09:46.50,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Good, old man, just like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.29,0:09:49.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why Beethoven?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.46,0:09:53.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, there's Beethoven{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} in this picture too!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.47,0:09:55.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.27,0:09:59.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was a picture that was secretly taken last night of this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.28,0:10:02.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is just about there...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.80,0:10:05.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, the statue of Beethoven isn't here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.52,0:10:09.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aha, I've figured out the caped phantom's trick!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.44,0:10:10.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.55,0:10:14.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right. The bust of Beethoven belongs in this room!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.69,0:10:16.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If this trick was used...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.57,0:10:21.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you think that beam fits the length of the stick?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.54,0:10:24.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.75,0:10:28.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doesn't the piece that was found\Nfit right into the crack over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.40,0:10:29.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.57,0:10:32.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's try it from the balcony on the other side.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.38,0:10:35.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Misaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, would you please lend us a fishing pole if you have one?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.80,0:10:37.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.57,0:10:41.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The eaves stick out more than the railing,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.94,0:10:44.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but if a fishing pole was used, it's simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.05,0:10:49.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The end of the string was tied in a loop, with a weight on the other end.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.99,0:10:55.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, the string was pulled under the railing...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.00,0:10:56.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Kobayashi.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.35,0:10:59.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please put your finger through the loop in the fishing line and hold it in place.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.38,0:11:00.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.92,0:11:04.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,May I borrow your coat, Inspector?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.37,0:11:08.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So now, we're all set.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.91,0:11:11.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Kobayashi.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.30,0:11:14.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Struggle with the phantom,\Nand let your hand go on my mark.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.81,0:11:16.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then pull the string.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.75,0:11:17.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.41,0:11:19.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.49,0:11:22.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, help!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.55,0:11:30.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now! Pull the string!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.98,0:11:35.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let the string go!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.25,0:11:45.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is fantastic! It's perfect!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.66,0:11:49.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! My coat!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.32,0:11:54.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That movement just now was exactly the same as Misaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s attacker...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.89,0:11:55.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.79,0:11:57.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You don't mean... it was you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.49,0:12:03.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In a dark room, it looked like the caped phantom fled.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.85,0:12:07.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, the victim and the attacker are one and the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.77,0:12:11.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer switches off the breaker in the corridor,\Ngoes back to her room right away,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.88,0:12:15.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,locks the door and screams.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.43,0:12:19.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, Misaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.71,0:12:22.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Misaki?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.85,0:12:27.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perfect, just as would be expected of a famous detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.04,0:12:29.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, all the pranks and threats I have received until now
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.60,0:12:31.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,are a matter of fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.87,0:12:35.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wanted you to believe me, so I put on an act...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.72,0:12:37.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.06,0:12:41.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But this is not directly connected to the murder of Mr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.75,0:12:42.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yoshinori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.55,0:12:45.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please come with me to the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.82,0:12:47.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.59,0:12:50.96,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This is not looking good.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.05,0:13:02.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.11,0:13:03.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The piano room?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.86,0:13:07.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan, what's up?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.54,0:13:08.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.50,0:13:17.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it now?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.15,0:13:18.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Megure.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.62,0:13:20.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please don't take him yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.26,0:13:21.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.38,0:13:23.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, {\i1}that thing{\i0}'s happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.89,0:13:26.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I've finally figured it out, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.48,0:13:30.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please look at the sword scratch on the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.57,0:13:33.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The angle of the scratch indicates\Nthat it fell perpendicularly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.01,0:13:35.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The result of the investigation shows likewise.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.68,0:13:39.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the railing of the spiral corridor by the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.10,0:13:42.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The scratch left on the tuning fork\Nthat Mr. Tenma was holding...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.90,0:13:45.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we connect all the traces left behind,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.24,0:13:48.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,we will discover a certain horrible trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.02,0:13:53.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There is a chandelier right above the scratch on the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.81,0:13:58.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That is, in fact, the last point\Nthat connects all the traces.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.90,0:14:00.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-You don't mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.62,0:14:01.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.98,0:14:05.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The sword that was suspended from that chandelier
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.55,0:14:09.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,fell straight down, pierced Mr. Tenma,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.26,0:14:12.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and left a perpendicular scratch on the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.55,0:14:14.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,O-Oh, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.91,0:14:16.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.40,0:14:19.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,even if he conveniently stood right under the place where the sword descended,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.27,0:14:22.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,wouldn't he have been stabbed in the head or the shoulder?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.16,0:14:25.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, Mr. Tenma was lying on his stomach.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.90,0:14:28.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No such thing could be done!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.65,0:14:31.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The answer to that mystery is the tuning fork.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.45,0:14:33.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tuning fork?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.83,0:14:36.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the piano bench.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.45,0:14:41.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The space between the piano and the bench is only enough for one person.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.10,0:14:43.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was the trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.91,0:14:47.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When Mr. Tenma came up\Nto the keys of the piano to play,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.45,0:14:49.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the bench was overturned beside the piano.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.50,0:14:54.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He also found the tuning fork used to tune the piano on the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.80,0:14:58.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, Mr. Tenma would naturally go to pick it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.59,0:15:03.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if so, he would turn his back to the sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.65,0:15:07.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the tuning fork that he picked up is the very thing that made the sword come falling.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.74,0:15:10.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.64,0:15:12.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This horrible trick...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.60,0:15:16.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was set up by placing a long string through the middle of the sword's handle,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.23,0:15:18.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then gathering both sides of the string,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.15,0:15:20.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,pulling them through the metal structure of the chandelier
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.82,0:15:24.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,using the railing of the spiral corridor as support.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.11,0:15:26.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One side was wound once around the large sofa,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.60,0:15:29.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then the tip of the string was attached to the tuning fork.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.40,0:15:32.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The other end of the string was left outside the window,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.37,0:15:34.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,with a weight attached to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.86,0:15:41.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After that, Mr. Tenma pulled the tuning fork out from under the chair.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.59,0:15:44.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The string that was attached to the tuning fork was released by the weight of the sword,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.91,0:15:49.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the heavy sword probably came falling in an instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.81,0:15:55.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the other hand, the fishing line that was holding the sword in place
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.38,0:15:59.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,was pulled by the weight suspended outside the window
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.25,0:16:02.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and dropped into the ocean below.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.64,0:16:05.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.00,0:16:07.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, who set all this up?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.40,0:16:09.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please recall...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.21,0:16:11.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The trick using the fishing line...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.20,0:16:16.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The method of throwing the evidence into the sea by using a heavy weight...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.26,0:16:21.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It is exactly like the one used with the caped phantom that was just demonstrated, is it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.67,0:16:25.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Misaki?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.50,0:16:30.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. The killer is {\i1}you{\i0}, Misaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.03,0:16:33.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After we all drank the wine,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.41,0:16:36.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you pretended to go to the kitchen,\Nbut you set your trap up here, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.94,0:16:40.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By raising the chandelier to the very top,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.48,0:16:43.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you made it harder to spot the sword,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.46,0:16:46.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,as well as increased its killing power, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.05,0:16:52.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought you were a great detective,\Nbut I guess I was wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.87,0:16:55.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you have proof that I did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.19,0:16:59.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd like you to take a look at the lid on top of the piano, and the stains inside it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.04,0:17:07.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is... wine?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.65,0:17:11.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Judging from the place where it is spilled,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.03,0:17:13.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it must have dripped when she opened the lid.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.80,0:17:18.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one who spilled the wine is the killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.65,0:17:20.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How can you be so sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.90,0:17:23.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because the wine is what Michel{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} brought from France,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.90,0:17:25.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and one that is not sold in Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.43,0:17:31.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. This is unmistakably the wine that I brought.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.40,0:17:36.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We were all drinking that wine.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.10,0:17:39.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Misaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is the only one who didn't drink it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.33,0:17:43.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I bumped into her and spilled the wine,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.77,0:17:47.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the wine that was probably left in the gap of her brooch
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.97,0:17:51.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,spilled out when she opened the lid on top of the piano.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.54,0:17:56.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You not only made it look like you were attacked by Mr. Tenma,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.62,0:17:59.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you set it up so that the picture of you two in the past would be found,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.68,0:18:01.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and tried to frame Yoshinori,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.67,0:18:05.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,who you figured would get angry and kill Mr. Tenma, isn't that right?{???}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.82,0:18:08.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Misaki, is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.81,0:18:12.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How are you going to explain\Nthe stalker incidents before all this?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.66,0:18:15.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She probably acted it out herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.59,0:18:18.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The prank call that came a while ago
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.35,0:18:23.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,was probably made by Misaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} herself from her cellular phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.01,0:18:26.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would she want to kill Tenma{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.42,0:18:31.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The date of that picture\Nof Mr. Tenma and Misaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.65,0:18:34.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,was only two weeks before her marriage, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.72,0:18:36.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-That's ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.31,0:18:45.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And "The Red Nocturne of Love" was a song that was written for you, ten years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.33,0:18:47.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Vraiment?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.65,0:18:50.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At first glance, the song appears to be a love song.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.92,0:18:52.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But in the language of flowers,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.34,0:19:01.14,Signs,,0,0,0,,Red Rose —\hBurning Passion
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.95,0:18:55.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,red roses symbolize burning passion,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.05,0:19:01.18,Signs,,0,0,0,,Marigold —\hHopelessness
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.70,0:18:57.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,marigolds symbolize hopelessness,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.16,0:18:58.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,lobelias malice,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.30,0:19:01.14,Signs,,0,0,0,,Lobelia —\hMalice
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.65,0:19:00.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and dahlias betrayal.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.53,0:19:01.06,Signs,,0,0,0,,Dahlia —\hBetrayal
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.67,0:19:06.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, this was a song of hate, written for someone who had betrayed one's lover!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.70,0:19:10.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that true, Misaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.42,0:19:13.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.75,0:19:15.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That day, ten years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.42,0:19:18.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he insisted on not leaving me,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.44,0:19:21.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so I called him out to a nearby beach
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.07,0:19:24.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and pushed him off a cliff.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.73,0:19:34.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then you married Yoshinori.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.60,0:19:38.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, Mr. Tenma miraculously survived,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.24,0:19:41.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,went overseas, and adopted a French name.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.16,0:19:44.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you found out Gerard Tenma's true identity,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.29,0:19:48.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you figured you had no choice but to kill Mr. Tenma again,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.76,0:19:53.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,in order to keep your previous crime from being revealed!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.85,0:19:59.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why did you try to frame Yoshinori as the killer?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.79,0:20:01.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was Masayo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s fault!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.11,0:20:05.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I got caught, my husband and the company would be taken away!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.35,0:20:10.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But a man in prison can't be taken away from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.70,0:20:14.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was planning to take over the company until he returned...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.67,0:20:16.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Misaki...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.50,0:20:20.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When Tenma{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s body wasn't found ten years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.54,0:20:24.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was always afraid that he might still be alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.14,0:20:27.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because I also knew the meaning of that song.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.38,0:20:34.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, the fact is, whenever Gerard sang that song at his concerts,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.27,0:20:36.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he would whisper the following phrase without fail.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.07,0:20:39.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Pour compenser ton cœur blessé.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.20,0:20:45.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In French, those words mean\N"To compensate your wounded heart."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.31,0:20:50.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The new arrangement had new lyrics,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.47,0:20:51.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but most probably...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.01,0:20:55.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes! Except for red roses,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.17,0:20:58.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the flowers have all been changed\Nto hyacinth, laurel and olive!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.20,0:21:03.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The flowers stand for sadness, peace and glory...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.18,0:21:08.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.61,0:21:12.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mr. Tenma, having realized that he had harassed Misaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} into trying to kill him,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.94,0:21:16.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,continued singing this song with feelings of compensation,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.40,0:21:19.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and probably deliberately decided\Nto sign a contract with the Kana Group.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.60,0:21:23.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. He once fell into the pit of grief,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.42,0:21:26.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but he no longer hated Misaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.25,0:21:28.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and having achieved success and happiness himself,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.96,0:21:32.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he probably wanted her to hear\Nthe {\i1}real{\i0} "Red Nocturne of Love".
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.74,0:23:14.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.91,0:23:17.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ever since then, I've been super-interested in the language of flowers.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.30,0:23:21.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Talk to you later, Sonoko. Bye-bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.32,0:23:23.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Welcome back.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.17,0:23:27.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here. I saw this at the flower shop, so I bought it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.79,0:23:30.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You bought that for me, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.96,0:23:32.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.24,0:23:36.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow, what pretty peach blossoms!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.17,0:23:39.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hm, this flower stands for...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.52,0:23:42.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"To be unrivaled in the world..."{this sounds awful. Catalan "invincible in fight". 天下無敵}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.05,0:23:48.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, what do you mean by this?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.50,0:23:51.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uh, well, you see...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.00,0:23:53.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just what do you mean,\N"to be unrivaled in the world"?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.69,0:23:56.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly that.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.81,0:24:10.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.62,0:24:14.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's get outside before they get into the elevator!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.76,0:24:18.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No use running away!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.35,0:24:22.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What I want to say is...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.25,0:24:24.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that you are an impostor!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.58,0:24:30.63,Signs,,0,0,0,,Next Conan:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.63,0:24:35.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint: Alphabet
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.56,0:24:41.51,Signs,,0,0,0,,Look forward to the next episode!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.78,0:24:37.41,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Next time, a nine-story apartment building!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.41,0:24:38.81,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Where the Detective Boys play a big part!
